Here is the cleaned up text:

**Service Cloud**

* Customize the Agent Experience
	+ Create the Voice Call Record Page: Add Service Cloud Voice components to show agents call features and related records.
	+ Set Up the Service Console App for Service Cloud Voice: Configure console app with Voice softphone, channel-object linking, and After Conversation Work.
	+ Configure the Phone Book for Outbound Calls: Let agents work off speed dial lists without DID numbers.
* Mask Customer Phone Numbers
* Respect Agent Capacity for Voice Calls (Beta): Route calls based on agent capacity.
* Sync Agent Presence Statuses Automatically
* Map Your Presence Statuses to Amazon Connect
* Grant Agents Access to View Agent Statuses When Transferring Calls
* Resolve Common Status Conflicts
* Customize Call Controls and Voice Extensions
	+ Build user interfaces and agent actions in Omni-Channel utility.
	+ Add Lightning Web Components, Lightning components, or Visualforce pages to softphone extension.
* Let Agents Pause and Resume Voice Call Recordings
* Set Up Desk Phones for Your Contact Center
* Set Up Voice Call Audio for Virtual Desktop Users
* Configure Caller ID: Create End User record using caller phone number.
* Customize Automatic Task Creation
* Set Up Voice ID: Use Voice ID powered by Amazon Connect to verify caller identity and detect fraud risk.
* Enable Agents To Test Their Workstations with Voice Status Utility: Verify browser, microphone, and virtual desktop infrastructure statuses.

**See Also**

* Add More Call Context with Screen Pop
* Customize Your Contact Center
* Customize the Supervisor Experience
title: Customizing Agent Experience in Service Cloud Voice
